IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: To communicate the Gospel of Jesus Christ, the supremacy of His Lordship, and a biblically informed view of the world.
IRS990.MissionDesc: 1) To proclaim the good news of the Gospel throughout the earth. 2) To teach and nurture His followers. 3) To equip and encourage believers to live out their faith. 4) To defend religious liberty by helping believers understand America's Christian heritage.
IRS990.Desc: Coral Ridge Ministries Media, Inc., dba D. James Kennedy Ministries, has several goals to communicate the fullness of the Gospel message, with love and without compromise, to use all available media and other ways yet undreamed of, to reach the world for Christ, to uphold standards of integrity, compassion, and above all, biblical fidelity, to pursue excellence in all things, and all things to the glory of God. The organization accomplishes these goals through the teaching of God's Word through radio, television, the printed word and other media, by assisting Christians in their spiritual growth by providing video, audio and printed resources, and by encouraging the application of biblical principles through media broadcasting. Millions of people are reached and served each year.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 11b Review of form 990 by governing body
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Form 990 is prepared by an independent CPA firm and reviewed by the chair of the organization's Finance Committee and the organization's top financial official. A copy of the final Form 990 is also provided to the voting members of the organization's governing body prior to its filing with the IRS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 12c Conflict of interest policy
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The organization requires all officers and board members to annually complete and sign a conflict of interest questionnaire. The chairperson of the board, or a committee, shall appoint a disinterested person or committee to review the signed statements and ensure that interested persons are in compliance with the conflict of interest policy. A disinterested person or committee reviews the board chairperson's signed statement. Should any potential conflicts of interest be disclosed, the board member or officer would be asked to refrain from participation in any deliberation or decision with regard to matters affected by the relationship.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 15a Process to establish compensation of top management official
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Independent members of the board of directors review comparability data from a GuideStar compensation report to determine the President/CEO's compensation was reasonable and within the range for the size of our organization. The committee followed the IRS rebuttable presumption checklist to compare appropriate salary data. The deliberation and decision process was documented in the minutes of the board meeting where compensation was considered and approved.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The governing documents, conflict of interest policy and financial statements are available upon request.
